            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) In nomine domini Dei omnipotentis aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/21">Berengarius divina favente clementia <rs
                                key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs></persName>. Quia sacerdotibus atque
                        levitis Christoque famulantibus temporalia dona regiae su[blimitati
                        conferre] omnimodis convenit, idcirco noverit omnium fidelium sanctae Dei
                        Ecclesiae nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac futurorum devota sollertia,
                            <persName key="#Intercessory #Count #compaterOf #fidelisOf"
                            ref="#people/166">Anselmum</persName> gloriosissimum <rs key="#Count"
                            >co[mitem</rs> dilectumque <rs key="#compaterOf">compatrem</rs> atque]
                            <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelem</rs> [nostrum suppliciter serenitatis
                        nostrae postulasse <rs key="#Intercessory">clementiam</rs>, quatenus quandam
                            <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Churches"
                            >capellam iuris regni nostri in honore beatissimi Petri apostolorum
                            principis</rs> dedicatam, in <geogName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#estates/124"><rs key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs> Veronensi
                        </geogName>existentem in <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#estates/181">loco qui [nominatur <rs
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                                    ><placeName key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Mention"
                                    ref="#places/400">ad Duos Robores</placeName></rs></geogName>]
                        de eodem [c]omitatu pertinentem, cum omnibus adiacentiis ac pertinentiis
                        suis in integrum, nec non et quendam <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Other_clerics #Royal_slave"
                            >clericum</rs> nomine <persName key="#Royal_slave">Leonem </persName>una
                        cum <rs key="#legallyRecognisedUnionWith">uxore</rs> et <rs
                            key="#sonOf #daughterOf">filiis ac filiabus suis</rs> pertinentem de
                        quandam curte eiusdem comitatus, sita videli[cet in prenominato] loco, [seu
                        et] quendam <rs key="#Mansi">mansum</rs> pertinentem <geogName
                            key="#Other_administrative_unit" ref="#estates/182"><rs
                                key="#Other_administrative_unit">de <placeName
                                    key="#Other_administrative_unit">sc[u]ldassia que
                                    Fluvium</placeName></rs></geogName> vocitatur, adiacentem in <rs
                            key="#Comitatus #Fines">confinio et territorio Veronensi</rs> loco ubi
                        nuncupatur <placeName>Runco Boniacum</placeName>, ex integro, sicut a <rs
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><persName key="#Agricultural_workers">quodam
                                Ursone</persName></rs> regi decernit[ur], cuidam <rs key="#Deacons"
                            >d[iacono</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">sanctae Ve]ro[nens]is ecclesiae
                            </rs></orgName>nomine <persName key="#Deacons" ref="#people/227"
                            >Adiberto, qui Audo</persName> vocatur, ob divine miserationis intuitum
                        nostraeque animae remedium per hanc nostrae auctoritatis inscriptionem iure
                        proprietario modis omnibus usque in perpetuum concedere dignaremur. Cuius
                        dignissimis precibus acclinati eandem capellam ad honorem beati Petri
                        constructam in prelibato loco existentem cum universis ad se aspicientibus
                        totoque <rs
                            key="#Domuscultae #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >domo cultili</rs> omnibusque <rs
                            key="#Massae #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >massariciis</rs>, casis quoque, terris, vineis, campis, pratis,
                        pascuis, sil[vis, salectis, sacionibus] <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >aquis aquarumque decursibus, paludibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >molendinis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >piscationibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Decima"
                            >decimis</rs> omnibusque <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Revenues"
                            >pensionibus</rs>, <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis etiam et
                            ancillis</rs>,<rs key="#Royal_aldius"> aldionibus ac aldianis </rs>et
                        utriusque sexus familiis, sive cum universis quae dici vel nominari possunt
                        ad ip[sam capellam pertinentibus] nec [non et predi]ctum servum nostrum
                        Leonem clericum de iam nominata curte pertinente[m] simul cum uxore et
                        filiis ac filiabus suis omnibusque eorum facultatibus tam acquisitis quam
                        acquirendis, seu et pretaxatum mansum in prenominato [Runco Boniaco positum]
                        ex integro, [prout] a iam nominato Ursone massario colitur, eidem Audiberto
                        diacono suisque heredibus presenti inscriptione perhenni iure concedimus
                        atque largimur, et de nostro iure in eius ius omnino transfundimus et
                        perdonamus, ut hab[eat, teneat,] possideat f[aciatque in] omnibus aliicquid
                        eius decreverit animus vel voluntas, potestatemque habeat donandi, vendendi,
                        alienandi, commutandi, pro anima iudicandi seu quicquid voluerit in omnibus
                        faciendi, amota totius potestatis in[quietudine vel minoratione.] Si quis
                        igitur hoc nostrae concessionis preceptum quandoque infringere aut violare
                        quesierit, ne inchoata perficere valeat, noverit se compositurum <rs
                            key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras centum,</rs> medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">camere palatii</rs> nostri et medietatem predicto
                        [Audiberto diacono suisque] heredibus ac proheredibus. Quod ut verius
                        credatur et diligentius observctur, manu propria subter roboravimus et anuli
                        nostri impressione assignari iussimus. Signum domni (MF) Berengarii
                        serenissimi regis. <persName key="#Chancellor">Ambrosius <rs
                                key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs></persName> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/216">Ardingi <rs
                                key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                                >archicancellarius</rs></persName> recognovi et subscripsi (SR) (SI
                        n. II) Data .X. kal. febr., anno domi[nicae] incarnationis .DCCCCV., domni
                        vero Berengarii piissimi regis .XVIII., indictione .VIIII, Actum in
                            <placeName key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Castle"
                            ref="#places/401"><rs
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Castle">Castro
                                Rupto</rs></placeName>. in Christi nomine felicit[er, amen]. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
